      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "c1",
          "point_value": 2,
          "description": "Correct integrand for volume",
          "official_rubric": "2 points: correct integrand. The diameter of each semicircular cross section equals $\\dfrac{20}{1+x^2} - 2$, so the radius is $\\dfrac{1}{2}\\left(\\dfrac{20}{1+x^2} - 2\\right)$. Area of semicircle $= \\dfrac{1}{2}\\pi r^2 = \\dfrac{\\pi}{8}\\left(\\dfrac{20}{1+x^2} - 2\\right)^2$.",
